Source: external-file
Section: database
Priority: optional
Maintainer: Ruohang Feng <rh@vonng.com>
Build-Depends: debhelper-compat (= 13), postgresql-all (>= 217~)
Standards-Version: 4.6.2
Rules-Requires-Root: no
Homepage: https://github.com/darold/external_file

Package: postgresql-PGVERSION-external-file
Architecture: any
Provides: postgresql-external-file
Depends: ${misc:Depends}, postgresql-PGVERSION
Description: Access external server-side files through PostgreSQL functions
 external_file adds an Oracle BFILE-like data type and helper functions that
 read or write files on the PostgreSQL server filesystem through controlled
 server-side large-object APIs. The extension installs into the fixed
 external_file schema and requires superuser privileges to create.
